				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello,
<br />

<br />
I think elgg's developers can answer this question better than I.
<br />

<br />
As the first step, I'd try the following:
<br />

<br />
* Upload the files bbantispam.php and bbas_config.php on the server, near the file &quot;index.php&quot;
<br />
* Edit the file &quot;index.php&quot;: insert as the first line:
<br />

<br />
&lt;?php include_once 'bbantispam.php'; ?&gt;
<br />

<br />
Hint: reset cookies often: if you answered a question. ATC remembers you are a human, and don't displays the question form anymore.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
<br />
Do you love our tools? <a href="https://www.plimus.com/jsp/buynow.jsp?contractId=1671485" target="_blank" class="postlink">Please sponsor</a> further development!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
